1) Suppose Abbi and Ilana want to have a fancy dinner date. Return all the restaurants that are Italian and $$$.

SELECT * 
FROM nomnom
WHERE cuisine = 'Italian'
  AND price = '$$$';

2) Your coworker Trey can’t remember the exact name of a restaurant he went to but  he knows it contains the word ‘meatball’ in it.

SELECT *
FROM nomnom
WHERE name LIKE '%meatball%';

3) Let’s order delivery to the house! Find all the close by spots in Midtown, Downtown or Chinatown.

SELECT * 
FROM nomnom
WHERE neighborhood = 'Midtown' 
  OR neighborhood = 'Downtown' 
  OR neighborhood = 'Chinatown';

4) Find all the health grade pending restaurants (empty values).

SELECT * 
FROM nomnom
WHERE health IS NULL; 

5) Create a Top 10 Restaurants Ranking based on reviews.

SELECT *
FROM nomnom
ORDER BY review DESC
LIMIT 10;

6) Use a CASE statement to change the rating system to:

SELECT name,
  CASE
    WHEN review > 4.5 THEN 'Extraordinary'
    WHEN review > 4 THEN 'Excellent'
    WHEN review > 3 THEN 'Good'
    WHEN review > 2 THEN 'Fair'
    ELSE 'Poor'
  END AS 'Review'
FROM nomnom;
